Ptolemy, 150AD.

A model of the solar system where the Earth is at the centre and plantes move on *epicycles* (roughly, orbits) along *deferents*. This "two orbit" model explained *apparent retrogade motion* of planets.

It was a very succesful mathematical model.

## Alternative models

* heliocentric model of Aristarchus, 270BC
* detailed heliocentric model of Copernicus, 1543

